Section 3: Roleplay / Personas

Example 3.1

User

You are a fitness coach. A client says they're too tired to work out.
AI Response

I hear you — and that's completely valid. Here's the secret: even a 10-minute light walk can boost your
energy more than resting. Let's just start gently today. Honor your body, but keep moving. You'll thank
yourself in 20 minutes, I promise.

Example 3.2

User

You are a doctor explaining a diagnosis to a patient.
AI Response

I want to make sure you fully understand what we found, so please stop me with any questions. Your tests
indicate elevated blood pressure. This is manageable — with lifestyle changes and, if needed, medication,
most people live completely normal, healthy lives. We'll create a plan together.

Example 3.3

User

You are a financial advisor. A young person asks how to start investing.
AI Response

Start early — that's the single best thing you can do. Build a 3-6 month emergency fund first. Then maximize
your 401(k) employer match — that's free money. Next, open a Roth IRA and invest in low-cost index funds.
Consistent contributions beat trying to time the market every time.

Example 3.4

User

You are a spaceship captain addressing your crew before launch.
AI Response

Crew of the Odyssey — in sixty minutes, we depart for the unknown. Every one of you was chosen for your
brilliance and courage. History will remember this mission. Stations, everyone. Let's make humanity proud.

Example 3.5

User

You are a pirate captain. Your crew demands more treasure.
AI Response

Arrr! Bold of ye to demand more from the captain who's kept every last one of ye alive and sailing! But I'm fair
— show me loyalty on the next voyage, and I'll split the haul 60-40 in yer favor. Cross me, and ye'll be
swabbing the poop deck for eternity. Do we have a deal?

Example 3.6

User

You are a Socratic philosopher questioning a student about truth.
AI Response

Tell me, friend — you say truth is what can be proven. But who determines the standard of proof? And if two
proofs contradict each other, which truth wins? I ask not to confound you — I ask because I too am



searching. Let us examine this together.

Example 3.7

User

You are a tour guide in Paris. Describe the Eiffel Tower.
AI Response

Welcome to the most iconic structure in the world — the Eiffel Tower! Built by Gustave Eiffel for the 1889
World's Fair, this iron lattice masterpiece stands 330 meters tall. Originally controversial, it became the
beloved symbol of Paris. On a clear day, you can see 70 kilometers from the top!

Example 3.8

User

You are a customer service agent. A customer says their laptop won't turn on.
AI Response

I'm sorry to hear that! Let's troubleshoot together. First, ensure the power cable is securely connected. Then
hold the power button for 10 full seconds, wait 30 seconds, and try again. Still no luck? I'll escalate this right
away.



Section 4: Coding Tasks

Example 4.1

User

Write a SQL query for the top 5 highest-paid employees.
AI Response
SELECT name, department, salary
FROM employees
ORDER BY salary DESC
LIMIT 5;

Example 4.2

User

Write a palindrome checker in Python.
AI Response
def is_palindrome(s):
s = s.replace(" ","").lower()
return s == s[::-1]

print(is_palindrome("racecar")) # True
print(is_palindrome("hello")) # False

Example 4.3

User

Write a Python quicksort implementation.
AI Response
def quicksort(arr):
if len(arr) <= 1: return arr
p = arr[len(arr)//2]
return quicksort([x for x in arr if x < p]) + \
[x for x in arr if x == p] + \
quicksort([x for x in arr if x > p])

Example 4.4

User

Write a Python function to parse a URL into components.
AI Response
from urllib.parse import urlparse

def parse_url(url):
p = urlparse(url)
return {"scheme":p.scheme,"host":p.netloc,"path":p.path,"query":p.query}

print(parse_url("https://example.com/page?q=1"))

Example 4.5

User

Write a two-sum function in Python.
AI Response
def two_sum(nums, target):
seen = {}



for i, n in enumerate(nums):
if target - n in seen: return (seen[target-n], i)
seen[n] = i

print(two_sum([2,7,11,15], 9)) # (0,1)

Example 4.6

User

Write a Python function to count vowels in a string.
AI Response
def count_vowels(s):
return sum(1 for c in s.lower() if c in "aeiou")

print(count_vowels("Hello World")) # 3

Example 4.7

User

Write a binary search function in Python.
AI Response
def binary_search(arr, target):
lo, hi = 0, len(arr) - 1
while lo <= hi:
mid = (lo + hi) // 2
if arr[mid] == target: return mid
elif arr[mid] < target: lo = mid + 1
else: hi = mid - 1
return -1

Example 4.8

User

Write a Python function to find the longest word in a string.
AI Response
def longest_word(s):
words = s.split()
return max(words, key=len) if words else ""

print(longest_word("The quick brown fox")) # "quick"

Example 4.9

User

Write a Python function to convert a list of tuples to a dictionary.
AI Response
def tuples_to_dict(lst):
return dict(lst)

print(tuples_to_dict([("a",1),("b",2)])) # {"a":1,"b":2}

